consideration of the specific provisions

Good afternoon Lance,

I=E2=80=99ve just tried to call =E2=80=93 could you please call when conven=
ient tomorrow.

Unfortunately, your letter doesn=E2=80=99t address the specific concerns th=
at Prendos has raised, or provide any consideration of the specific provisi=
ons which Tower says exempt all the work.

Apart from perhaps the floor joists mentioned at paragraph 4.a. of your let=
ter, which are arguable / discretionary based on damage and interpretation,=
 the rest of the works are specifically excluded from the exemptions in Sch=
edule 1. The general =E2=80=98maintenance=E2=80=99 provisions of schedule 1=
 item 1 do not override the specific exclusions in the rest of the Schedule=
. Especially when all the work is being undertaken at once. Just one exampl=
e is the internal load bearing and bracing walls:

[cid:image027.jpg@01DCC26E.87BACE30]
I will happily talk you through the specific provisions of the Building Act=
 schedule 1 if that would assist, but we do not accept that this work can b=
e carried out without consent. If you have taken expert advice on this cons=
enting, please provide it. Otherwise, please reconsider your position.

Kind regards

[cid:image028.png@01DCC26E.87BACE30]
Richard Hargreaves
