Hello Raffaella,
Thank you for the email below.
We can confirm that testing can commence at 2pm on Friday October 17.
We will test from sample sites as required to complete a full and thorough =
determination of any potential contamination, inclusive of all the areas wh=
ich you have referred to below.
You may undertake your own independent testing at any stage; however, Tower=
 would only consider reimbursement for testing which is - a) claim related =
& b) testing which is outside of that which Tower will complete.
I am confident that the Tower Insurance testing will be transparent, quanti=
fied by lab results, and adequate to provide comfort for all parties.

Clarified scope of testing as follows:

  1.  150mm diameter inspection portals cut in wall cavities of every room =
on the first floor at a height of 300 mm of floor level and directly undern=
eath the top plate.
  2.  Testing of the roof cavity at the soffit junction where potential con=
taminants may have risen through the wall cavity. Testing of the roof cavit=
y at the apex where smoke may have accumulated.
  3.  Testing of the underside of the rear large upper deck.
  4.  Testing of the basement utilizing all exposed framing cavities and 15=
0mm testing portals cut into any remining ceiling linings in the basemen ar=
ea.
  5.  Any additional sample sites that we feel are required during testing.

To ensure effectual testing it would be beneficial if you could confirm the=
 following:

  1.  That the chlorine was located in the laundry room downstairs at the t=
ime of the fire.
  2.  The quantity of the chlorine that was in that room at the time of the=
 fire.
  3.  Where there any other chemicals that were located in that same room, =
or anywhere else downstairs.


Beyond completing testing and providing laboratory results as described abo=
ve, I am certain the most productive action we can make towards progressing=
 the claim is to have a meeting where we can discuss the overall claim resp=
onse process, providing a forum for you to table any questions, or concerns=
 that you may hold. Those concerns can be responded to, and the responses c=
an be documented via minutes with actions and agreements detailed in the mi=
nutes providing a framework for moving forward with a pre-agreed and produc=
tive pathway. I believe this would be very worthwhile and will provide us a=
ll with detail, clarity, and documentation that we can all use to our benef=
it.
Your lawyers and advisors would of course be welcome to attend this meeting.

I look forward to seeing you again on Friday.
Kind Regards,
Grant.

